what you consider

00:01:13.770 --> 00:01:17.970 align:middle line:84%
to be the key to consciousness
within your studies

00:01:17.970 --> 00:01:20.790 align:middle line:84%
throughout your lifetime
and the consciousness

00:01:20.790 --> 00:01:22.980 align:middle line:84%
and the communication
pathways with God.

00:01:22.980 --> 00:01:25.210 align:middle line:84%
Can you explain that just
a little bit, just kind of

00:01:25.210 --> 00:01:28.120 align:middle line:84%
set up the context for the
rest of the conversation?

00:01:28.120 --> 00:01:31.440 align:middle line:10%
>>BAKST: I began my
spiritual journey

00:01:31.440 --> 00:01:34.900 align:middle line:10%
when I was around
17 or 18 years old.

00:01:34.900 --> 00:01:39.710 align:middle line:10%
I'm a total product of the
'60s from Southern California.

00:01:39.710 --> 00:01:42.940 align:middle line:84%
And I was exposed to everything
that was going on back then,

00:01:42.940 --> 00:01:47.000 align:middle line:84%
from psychedelics to Eastern
influence, yoga, Kundalini.

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:50.910 align:middle line:90%
And it woke up my soul.

00:01:50.910 --> 00:01:56.250 align:middle line:84%
I then went to visit the
land of Israel ostensibly

00:01:56.250 --> 00:02:00.220 align:middle line:84%
to study the Kabbalah,
not really even knowing

00:02:00.220 --> 00:02:02.190 align:middle line:90%
what it was at the time.

00:02:02.190 --> 00:02:05.680 align:middle line:84%
And forgetting one
little technicality,

00:02:05.680 --> 00:02:08.310 align:middle line:84%
and that is that back
then hardly anything

00:02:08.310 --> 00:02:09.979 align:middle line:84%
was available in
English, and I was not

00:02:09.979 --> 00:02:12.000 align:middle line:90%
speaking Hebrew at the time.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.770 align:middle line:84%
And I then enrolled
in a yeshiva,

00:02:16.770 --> 00:02:23.300 align:middle line:84%
which is a rabbinical
seminary, and they did not

00:02:23.300 --> 00:02:25.210 align:middle line:90%
offer Kabbalah.

00:02:25.210 --> 00:02:29.575 align:middle line:84%
They offered Talmud,
Halakhah, that's Jewish law,

00:02:29.575 --> 00:02:32.240 align:middle line:84%
and the Musar,
the Jewish ethics.

00:02:32.240 --> 00:02:36.320 align:middle line:84%
And I was told again
and again that you

00:02:36.320 --> 00:02:40.530 align:middle line:84%
have to first build
your foundation

00:02:40.530 --> 00:02:44.270 align:middle line:84%
with the traditional tools
of the Jewish religion

00:02:44.270 --> 00:02:45.520 align:middle line:90%
before you begin the Kabbalah.

00:02:45.520 --> 00:02:46.853 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Which was interesting.

00:02:46.853 --> 00:02:48.940 align:middle line:84%
You were atheist at
this point still, right?

00:02:48.940 --> 00:02:53.210 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: I was an atheist
regarding any established

00:02:53.210 --> 00:02:53.710 align:middle line:90%
religion.

00:02:53.710 --> 00:02:54.910 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right, right.

00:02:54.910 --> 00:02:56.125 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: If I'm on
a spiritual search--

00:02:56.125 --> 00:02:56.975 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Any kind of
the classic-- yeah.

00:02:56.975 --> 00:02:58.480 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yes, totally, totally.

00:02:58.480 --> 00:03:02.890 align:middle line:84%
I mean, back earlier
in what amounted

00:03:02.890 --> 00:03:04.970 align:middle line:84%
to like religious
Hebrew school, I

00:03:04.970 --> 00:03:06.460 align:middle line:90%
was known as the class atheist.

00:03:06.460 --> 00:03:07.256 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:03:07.256 --> 00:03:08.380 align:middle line:90%
That's why I brought it up.

00:03:08.380 --> 00:03:09.810 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yes.

00:03:09.810 --> 00:03:12.950 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So now you happened to
kind of dive into the deep end

00:03:12.950 --> 00:03:14.177 align:middle line:90%
pretty quickly.

00:03:14.177 --> 00:03:14.760 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yeah.

00:03:14.760 --> 00:03:20.640 align:middle line:84%
So I spent a good 12 years,
day and night, six days a week.

00:03:20.640 --> 00:03:23.980 align:middle line:84%
There's no two-day
weekend in Israel.

00:03:23.980 --> 00:03:29.200 align:middle line:84%
And I mastered Hebrew
and Aramaic and Talmud

00:03:29.200 --> 00:03:31.430 align:middle line:90%
and Jewish law, as I mentioned.

00:03:31.430 --> 00:03:37.540 align:middle line:84%
And then I slowly began to
study the Kabbalah with teachers

00:03:37.540 --> 00:03:40.240 align:middle line:90%
and from books and colleagues.

00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:44.200 align:middle line:84%
And as I developed
those tools, it

00:03:44.200 --> 00:03:51.900 align:middle line:84%
enabled me actually to go
in the direction consciously

00:03:51.900 --> 00:03:55.710 align:middle line:84%
where I began-- when I woke
up at 17, 18 years old.

00:03:55.710 --> 00:03:57.709 align:middle line:84%
I actually found a
book of Hatha yoga

00:03:57.709 --> 00:03:59.500 align:middle line:84%
that my mother had in
the house, and that's

00:03:59.500 --> 00:04:00.300 align:middle line:90%
what started the whole thing.

00:04:00.300 --> 00:04:02.850 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Like Jessie Stearn,
"Yoga, Life, and Reincarnation"

00:04:02.850 --> 00:04:03.600 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yes, yes.

00:04:03.600 --> 00:04:06.260 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I know that got a
whole generation of people

00:04:06.260 --> 00:04:07.370 align:middle line:90%
on the path.

00:04:07.370 --> 00:04:10.400 align:middle line:90%
It was a good guess.

00:04:10.400 --> 00:04:18.160 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: And so my studies
led me to a deep investigation

00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:21.290 align:middle line:84%
for learning the
fundamentals of the Kabbalah.

00:04:21.290 --> 00:04:24.592 align:middle line:84%
And let me just explain
about the term "Kabbalah."

00:04:24.592 --> 00:04:28.540 align:middle line:84%
It means as much as the
word "science" means.

00:04:28.540 --> 00:04:30.740 align:middle line:84%
One man's science is
another man's witchcraft.

00:04:30.740 --> 00:04:32.790 align:middle line:84%
There are so many
fields of science.

00:04:32.790 --> 00:04:35.380 align:middle line:84%
Likewise, Kabbalah
is not a thing.

00:04:35.380 --> 00:04:36.780 align:middle line:90%
It's not one thing at all.

00:04:36.780 --> 00:04:38.460 align:middle line:90%
There are many different fields.

00:04:38.460 --> 00:04:42.170 align:middle line:84%
As many fields as there
are in modern science,

00:04:42.170 --> 00:04:44.342 align:middle line:84%
believe it or not, there
are in the Kabbalah.

00:04:44.342 --> 00:04:46.050 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, this
is my next question.

00:04:46.050 --> 00:04:50.430 align:middle line:84%
I want to get into definitions,
because for non-Jewish viewers,

00:04:50.430 --> 00:04:53.700 align:middle line:84%
we don't have really much of an
idea what a lot of this means.

00:04:53.700 --> 00:04:54.680 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: Let me tell
you a little secret.

00:04:54.680 --> 00:04:55.160 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:04:55.160 --> 00:04:56.650 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: For most
Jewish viewers also.

00:04:56.650 --> 00:04:57.775 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You don't either.

00:04:57.775 --> 00:04:58.780 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:04:58.780 --> 00:05:02.310 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's interesting because
I think in the Western world,

00:05:02.310 --> 00:05:05.640 align:middle line:84%
most non-Jews heard the word
"Kabbalah" or "Kabbalah"

00:05:05.640 --> 00:05:07.320 align:middle line:84%
the first time
because of Madonna.

00:05:07.320 --> 00:05:08.210 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Exactly.

00:05:08.210 --> 00:05:09.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I mean, really.

00:05:09.300 --> 00:05:10.270 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: It's out.

00:05:10.270 --> 00:05:10.850 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:05:10.850 --> 00:05:12.290 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Madonna
brought it forward.

00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:13.210 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: The cat
is out of the bag.

00:05:13.210 --> 00:05:14.170 align:middle line:90%
But the question is--

00:05:14.170 --> 00:05:14.540 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: What is it?

00:05:14.540 --> 00:05:15.679 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: --what is the cat?

00:05:15.679 --> 00:05:16.220 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:05:16.220 --> 00:05:18.720 align:middle line:84%
So what I'd like to do, if
you don't mind at this point,

00:05:18.720 --> 00:05:21.657 align:middle line:84%
you can give us a little bit
of a religious lesson here--

00:05:21.657 --> 00:05:22.240 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Sure.

00:05:22.240 --> 00:05:25.020 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --and leading
up to the Kabbalah.

00:05:25.020 --> 00:05:28.520 align:middle line:84%
And that is telling us the
difference between the Talmud,

00:05:28.520 --> 00:05:31.257 align:middle line:84%
the Torah, and ultimately,
what is the Kabbalah?

00:05:31.257 --> 00:05:32.590 align:middle line:90%
You just explained a little bit.

00:05:32.590 --> 00:05:34.320 align:middle line:90%
It's like the word "science."

00:05:34.320 --> 00:05:37.600 align:middle line:84%
But let's have some history
so we know what we're not

00:05:37.600 --> 00:05:39.150 align:middle line:90%
talking about and what we are.

00:05:39.150 --> 00:05:40.910 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yes.

00:05:40.910 --> 00:05:44.422 align:middle line:84%
The word "Torah"
means "teachings."

00:05:44.422 --> 00:05:47.590 align:middle line:90%
It means education.

00:05:47.590 --> 00:05:50.270 align:middle line:90%
It means transmission.

00:05:50.270 --> 00:05:53.480 align:middle line:84%
And the Torah essentially
has three different meanings.

00:05:53.480 --> 00:05:55.150 align:middle line:84%
It's most specific
meaning, it refers

00:05:55.150 --> 00:05:59.950 align:middle line:84%
to the Five Books of Moses known
as the Pentateuch-- Genesis

00:05:59.950 --> 00:06:01.060 align:middle line:90%
through Deuteronomy.

00:06:01.060 --> 00:06:03.530 align:middle line:84%
And that's the main
meaning of the Torah.

00:06:03.530 --> 00:06:08.430 align:middle line:84%
Then, by extension, Torah also
refers to all the other books

00:06:08.430 --> 00:06:10.464 align:middle line:84%
of what in the
Christian Western world

00:06:10.464 --> 00:06:11.630 align:middle line:90%
they call the Old Testament.

00:06:11.630 --> 00:06:13.338 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's what
I was going to ask.

00:06:13.338 --> 00:06:15.310 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: OK?

00:06:15.310 --> 00:06:17.930 align:middle line:84%
And Judaism consists
of 24 books.

00:06:17.930 --> 00:06:20.770 align:middle line:84%
And they include the Prophets
and the other books like Psalms

00:06:20.770 --> 00:06:23.370 align:middle line:84%
and Proverbs, the
Book of Daniel,

00:06:23.370 --> 00:06:26.160 align:middle line:90%
and the Book of Chronicles.

00:06:26.160 --> 00:06:26.800 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:06:26.800 --> 00:06:30.100 align:middle line:84%
So that's also
Torah, by extension--

00:06:30.100 --> 00:06:35.009 align:middle line:84%
refers to all of those three
books, which together are 24.

00:06:35.009 --> 00:06:35.550 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:06:35.550 --> 00:06:37.230 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: Then, and
most importantly,

00:06:37.230 --> 00:06:40.000 align:middle line:84%
the term "Torah," by
further extension,

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:44.250 align:middle line:84%
refers to the very
vast oral tradition.

00:06:44.250 --> 00:06:47.640 align:middle line:84%
There's an oral Torah along
with the written Torah.

00:06:47.640 --> 00:06:51.640 align:middle line:90%
Now, why must this be so?

00:06:51.640 --> 00:06:53.040 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look
at the Godhead.

00:06:53.040 --> 00:06:53.790 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:06:53.790 --> 00:06:56.480 align:middle line:84%
Everyone's aware of
this concept that man

00:06:56.480 --> 00:06:58.280 align:middle line:90%
is made in the image of God.

00:06:58.280 --> 00:06:59.120 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:06:59.120 --> 00:07:01.410 align:middle line:84%
Well, we know now,
in the last 40 years,

00:07:01.410 --> 00:07:04.970 align:middle line:84%
we really have two brains and
two hemispheres in our brain,

00:07:04.970 --> 00:07:07.900 align:middle line:84%
and they process information
in two very different ways.

00:07:07.900 --> 00:07:12.360 align:middle line:84%
We have the left brain that's
essentially analytical, linear,

00:07:12.360 --> 00:07:14.710 align:middle line:90%
binary.

00:07:14.710 --> 00:07:20.180 align:middle line:84%
Whereas the right brain
is unitive, circular.

00:07:20.180 --> 00:07:20.950 align:middle line:90%
Likewise--

00:07:20.950 --> 00:07:23.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Credited with
being the more creative part.

00:07:23.800 --> 00:07:26.300 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yes.

00:07:26.300 --> 00:07:30.310 align:middle line:84%
But really, we would want to say
there's two modes of creativity

00:07:30.310 --> 00:07:30.810 align:middle line:90%
in here.

00:07:30.810 --> 00:07:30.956 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:07:30.956 --> 00:07:32.748 align:middle line:84%
I mean, one certainly
influences the other.

00:07:32.748 --> 00:07:33.580 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Absolutely.

00:07:33.580 --> 00:07:34.210 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:07:34.210 --> 00:07:38.806 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: And this is precisely
why there are two Torahs.

00:07:38.806 --> 00:07:39.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Two Torahs.

00:07:39.680 --> 00:07:39.900 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:07:39.900 --> 00:07:40.300 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Two Torahs.

00:07:40.300 --> 00:07:41.060 align:middle line:90%
Who ever heard of that?

00:07:41.060 --> 00:07:41.440 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's the first
I ever heard of two Torahs.

00:07:41.440 --> 00:07:41.775 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: I know.

00:07:41.775 --> 00:07:42.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:07:42.170 --> 00:07:43.090 align:middle line:90%
So what's the other Torah?

00:07:43.090 --> 00:07:43.460 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: OK.

00:07:43.460 --> 00:07:44.330 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: There's
the oral and there's

00:07:44.330 --> 00:07:46.480 align:middle line:84%
the one that's kind of the
Old Testament and more.

00:07:46.480 --> 00:07:46.930 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yeah.

00:07:46.930 --> 00:07:47.650 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Then there's the oral.

00:07:47.650 --> 00:07:49.816 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: And that's called
the written and the oral.

00:07:49.816 --> 00:07:51.970 align:middle line:84%
Because we're made
in the image of God,

00:07:51.970 --> 00:07:56.120 align:middle line:84%
which means when the Godhead,
as much as we can try to express

00:07:56.120 --> 00:07:59.350 align:middle line:84%
that, which we cannot,
OK, iterates itself,

00:07:59.350 --> 00:08:04.160 align:middle line:84%
makes copies of itself, it makes
the human being in its image.

00:08:04.160 --> 00:08:08.890 align:middle line:84%
We precisely have two modes
of information processing

00:08:08.890 --> 00:08:14.740 align:middle line:84%
because the divine mind has
two modes of processing.

00:08:14.740 --> 00:08:16.150 align:middle line:90%
And we're just replicating that.

00:08:16.150 --> 00:08:21.040 align:middle line:84%
Therefore, Torah is considered
to be the mind of God,

00:08:21.040 --> 00:08:22.770 align:middle line:90%
the thoughts of God.

00:08:22.770 --> 00:08:25.750 align:middle line:84%
If God, the Godhead,
has two hemispheres,

00:08:25.750 --> 00:08:29.000 align:middle line:84%
two modes of processing,
therefore the Torah,

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:33.020 align:middle line:84%
by definition, must
have two modes as well.

00:08:33.020 --> 00:08:35.380 align:middle line:84%
They are the written and
the oral, the written

00:08:35.380 --> 00:08:38.059 align:middle line:84%
corresponding, in general,
to the left hemisphere.

00:08:38.059 --> 00:08:38.559 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:08:38.559 --> 00:08:40.500 align:middle line:90%
As it processes, it's linear.

00:08:40.500 --> 00:08:44.340 align:middle line:84%
The written Torah is just the
letters that are written down,

00:08:44.340 --> 00:08:46.921 align:middle line:84%
which are black ink
upon white parchment.

00:08:46.921 --> 00:08:47.420 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:08:47.420 --> 00:08:50.620 align:middle line:84%
In the original
scroll of the Torah,

00:08:50.620 --> 00:08:53.340 align:middle line:90%
there's no vowels written.

00:08:53.340 --> 00:08:55.360 align:middle line:84%
That's all part of
the oral Torah that's

00:08:55.360 --> 00:08:57.530 align:middle line:90%
superimposed upon the written.

00:08:57.530 --> 00:09:00.640 align:middle line:84%
It's just like a binary
computer printout.

00:09:00.640 --> 00:09:01.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:09:01.330 --> 00:09:06.760 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: The right
hemisphere is the oral Torah.

00:09:06.760 --> 00:09:10.910 align:middle line:84%
And the oral Torah, just like
with our two hemispheres,

00:09:10.910 --> 00:09:11.960 align:middle line:90%
they work independent.

00:09:11.960 --> 00:09:16.490 align:middle line:84%
But there are united
via the corpus callosum,

00:09:16.490 --> 00:09:19.390 align:middle line:84%
a network of several
hundred nerves, wires,

00:09:19.390 --> 00:09:21.000 align:middle line:90%
that connect the two.

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:22.190 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:09:22.190 --> 00:09:27.700 align:middle line:84%
True Torah learning cannot be
without both of the hemispheres

00:09:27.700 --> 00:09:31.030 align:middle line:90%
working together simultaneously.

00:09:31.030 --> 00:09:38.810 align:middle line:84%
And therefore in traditional
Torah, it's silly at best,

00:09:38.810 --> 00:09:41.630 align:middle line:84%
it's absurd and even
tragic at worst,

00:09:41.630 --> 00:09:46.050 align:middle line:84%
that anyone would think they
can open up the written Torah,

00:09:46.050 --> 00:09:48.630 align:middle line:84%
known in the world
as the Old Testament,

00:09:48.630 --> 00:09:53.789 align:middle line:84%
and read it and expect to truly
understand what it's saying.

00:09:53.789 --> 00:09:54.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:09:54.330 --> 00:09:56.510 align:middle line:84%
So that brings up a
rash of questions.

00:09:56.510 --> 00:10:00.140 align:middle line:84%
One of them is, then have the
two been combined into written

00:10:00.140 --> 00:10:03.550 align:middle line:84%
form so that a novice
can pick up and begin

00:10:03.550 --> 00:10:06.970 align:middle line:84%
integrating the oral and
the written, so to speak,

00:10:06.970 --> 00:10:08.030 align:middle line:90%
in the written language?

00:10:08.030 --> 00:10:10.359 align:middle line:84%
I mean, like vowels-- replete
with vowels and things.

00:10:10.359 --> 00:10:11.150 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Precisely.

00:10:11.150 --> 00:10:14.080 align:middle line:90%
So now enter Talmud.

00:10:14.080 --> 00:10:14.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:10:14.690 --> 00:10:15.190 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:10:15.190 --> 00:10:19.800 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: Talmud, in
general, is the summation

00:10:19.800 --> 00:10:24.160 align:middle line:84%
of the oral Torah,
originally the oral Torah.

00:10:24.160 --> 00:10:27.154 align:middle line:84%
Everyone thinks that when
Moses was on Mount Sinai,

00:10:27.154 --> 00:10:28.320 align:middle line:90%
he got the Ten Commandments.

00:10:28.320 --> 00:10:30.589 align:middle line:84%
It was so much,
much more than that.

00:10:30.589 --> 00:10:32.630 align:middle line:84%
Remember, he was up there
for 40 days, 40 nights.

00:10:32.630 --> 00:10:33.710 align:middle line:90%
What was he doing?

00:10:33.710 --> 00:10:34.440 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:10:34.440 --> 00:10:37.720 align:middle line:90%
He was receiving the oral Torah.

00:10:37.720 --> 00:10:41.460 align:middle line:84%
He was being taught by
the divine mind itself.

00:10:41.460 --> 00:10:43.340 align:middle line:84%
Now, originally,
it was forbidden

00:10:43.340 --> 00:10:45.550 align:middle line:84%
to write down the oral
Torah because part

00:10:45.550 --> 00:10:48.940 align:middle line:84%
of the idea of
oral is that-- it's

00:10:48.940 --> 00:10:52.270 align:middle line:84%
like if we took a snapshot of
this right here going on right

00:10:52.270 --> 00:10:54.590 align:middle line:90%
now and that's all you knew.

00:10:54.590 --> 00:10:56.000 align:middle line:84%
You can show that
to 1,000 people

00:10:56.000 --> 00:10:58.330 align:middle line:84%
and get 1,000
interpretations of that.

00:10:58.330 --> 00:10:59.170 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:10:59.170 --> 00:11:05.800 align:middle line:84%
So it had to remain oral,
live, like a running video.

00:11:05.800 --> 00:11:09.300 align:middle line:84%
However, beginning in the second
century after the Common Era,

00:11:09.300 --> 00:11:13.610 align:middle line:84%
due to the persecutions, the
exile, the whole breakdown

00:11:13.610 --> 00:11:17.590 align:middle line:84%
of the transmission system
from master to disciple,

00:11:17.590 --> 00:11:22.980 align:middle line:84%
it was then divine permission
was given to write down

00:11:22.980 --> 00:11:24.630 align:middle line:90%
parts of the oral Torah.

00:11:24.630 --> 00:11:29.189 align:middle line:84%
So yes, Regina, the oral
Torah now is all written down.

00:11:29.189 --> 00:11:29.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:11:29.730 --> 00:11:31.040 align:middle line:90%
So now I have two questions.

00:11:31.040 --> 00:11:32.420 align:middle line:90%
Let's go back to Moses.

00:11:32.420 --> 00:11:35.542 align:middle line:84%
Now, if Moses was historically
part of an Egyptian lineage,

00:11:35.542 --> 00:11:37.500 align:middle line:84%
it makes sense he wouldn't
be writing this down

00:11:37.500 --> 00:11:38.590 align:middle line:90%
in Hebrew, right?

00:11:38.590 --> 00:11:41.750 align:middle line:84%
I mean, according
to some history,

00:11:41.750 --> 00:11:46.180 align:middle line:84%
he was part of a royal
Egyptian family who

00:11:46.180 --> 00:11:51.510 align:middle line:84%
then came into being as
a representative and one

00:11:51.510 --> 00:11:55.400 align:middle line:84%
who was bringing information
in for the new clan, the Hebrew

00:11:55.400 --> 00:11:56.040 align:middle line:90%
clan.

00:11:56.040 --> 00:11:57.710 align:middle line:84%
And so I always
wondered, how does

00:11:57.710 --> 00:12:00.140 align:middle line:84%
that transmission
occur that ultimately

00:12:00.140 --> 00:12:01.829 align:middle line:90%
came to be in Hebrew?

00:12:01.829 --> 00:12:03.370 align:middle line:84%
There had to be a
way of transmitting

00:12:03.370 --> 00:12:06.240 align:middle line:84%
via kind of very pure
thoughts and concepts,

00:12:06.240 --> 00:12:08.710 align:middle line:84%
so to speak, in order
for him to even integrate

00:12:08.710 --> 00:12:12.451 align:middle line:84%
that enough to be able to share
it and pass this knowledge on,

00:12:12.451 --> 00:12:12.950 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:12:12.950 --> 00:12:13.220 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yes.

00:12:13.220 --> 00:12:15.469 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because there's a
language barrier of sorts.

00:12:15.469 --> 00:12:18.340 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: So whatever
Moses received

00:12:18.340 --> 00:12:22.750 align:middle line:84%
from his Egyptian
heritage, that was greatly

00:12:22.750 --> 00:12:26.430 align:middle line:84%
augmented by what
he then received

00:12:26.430 --> 00:12:30.310 align:middle line:84%
through the direct transmission
on Mount Sinai, which

00:12:30.310 --> 00:12:34.420 align:middle line:84%
not only included the written
Torah, the Five Books of Moses

00:12:34.420 --> 00:12:39.120 align:middle line:84%
but also this very,
very vast oral Torah.

00:12:39.120 --> 00:12:42.560 align:middle line:84%
That is everything that's
written in between the lines.

00:12:42.560 --> 00:12:44.310 align:middle line:90%
It qualifies everything.

00:12:44.310 --> 00:12:47.474 align:middle line:84%
It's really absurd to think
that we can read-- take

00:12:47.474 --> 00:12:48.640 align:middle line:90%
a look at the written Torah.

00:12:48.640 --> 00:12:50.750 align:middle line:84%
There are things
in there that are

00:12:50.750 --> 00:12:55.470 align:middle line:90%
mentioned in one brief passing.

00:12:55.470 --> 00:12:58.370 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't really mean
anything in and of itself

00:12:58.370 --> 00:13:02.747 align:middle line:84%
until we bring in all
the vast information

00:13:02.747 --> 00:13:04.330 align:middle line:84%
from the oral tradition
of what that--

00:13:04.330 --> 00:13:05.280 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
what I'm saying.

00:13:05.280 --> 00:13:06.446 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: --intended to mean.

00:13:06.446 --> 00:13:08.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so
if he's receiving

00:13:08.100 --> 00:13:14.270 align:middle line:84%
a divine, pure transmission,
it goes beyond language anyway.

00:13:14.270 --> 00:13:14.920 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yes.

00:13:14.920 --> 00:13:17.240 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You're being
downloaded with direct concepts

00:13:17.240 --> 00:13:20.520 align:middle line:84%
and understandings that can then
be translated down the road.

00:13:20.520 --> 00:13:23.410 align:middle line:84%
But as you say, over the
next however many years,

00:13:23.410 --> 00:13:25.800 align:middle line:84%
the translation started
becoming corrupted,

00:13:25.800 --> 00:13:28.150 align:middle line:84%
which happens as you pass
stories down from generation

00:13:28.150 --> 00:13:29.160 align:middle line:90%
to generation, right?

00:13:29.160 --> 00:13:29.340 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: No.

00:13:29.340 --> 00:13:30.890 align:middle line:84%
I didn't say it
became corrupted.

00:13:30.890 --> 00:13:31.910 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:13:31.910 --> 00:13:36.560 align:middle line:84%
To the contrary, the
Torah, the oral Torah,

00:13:36.560 --> 00:13:40.175 align:middle line:84%
has a built-in system
that's self-correcting.

00:13:40.175 --> 00:13:41.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, what
does that tell us?

00:13:41.800 --> 00:13:43.466 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: Well, it's
a whole methodology.

00:13:43.466 --> 00:13:46.290 align:middle line:84%
This is what's very
little known in the world.

00:13:46.290 --> 00:13:48.940 align:middle line:84%
Torah, in this sense,
is not a religion

00:13:48.940 --> 00:13:53.900 align:middle line:84%
based upon feelings and ideas
and speculations and theories.

00:13:53.900 --> 00:13:56.050 align:middle line:90%
It's really a hard science.

00:13:56.050 --> 00:14:00.170 align:middle line:84%
And it comes with an
extensive methodology

00:14:00.170 --> 00:14:04.740 align:middle line:84%
of how-- when we open up
the written Torah-- how

00:14:04.740 --> 00:14:06.440 align:middle line:90%
do we now decipher?

00:14:06.440 --> 00:14:07.660 align:middle line:90%
It's all code.

00:14:07.660 --> 00:14:08.980 align:middle line:90%
That's a computer code.

00:14:08.980 --> 00:14:11.770 align:middle line:84%
And in truth, even though
it says "In the beginning,

00:14:11.770 --> 00:14:15.700 align:middle line:84%
God created--" the truth is
what is being revealed there

00:14:15.700 --> 00:14:20.580 align:middle line:84%
on the surface is nothing
more than-- remember

00:14:20.580 --> 00:14:25.260 align:middle line:84%
in "2001 Space Odyssey," the
monkey men, the black obelisk?

00:14:25.260 --> 00:14:28.000 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:29.520 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: They could touch it.

00:14:29.520 --> 00:14:32.647 align:middle line:84%
They didn't have a
clue what it was.

00:14:32.647 --> 00:14:33.730 align:middle line:90%
It is not an exaggeration.

00:14:33.730 --> 00:14:36.271 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So you're saying it's
like a binary code literally.

00:14:36.271 --> 00:14:37.430 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yeah.

00:14:37.430 --> 00:14:41.930 align:middle line:84%
And the methodology
is very specific.

00:14:41.930 --> 00:14:43.910 align:middle line:84%
There are rules,
just like in science.

00:14:43.910 --> 00:14:47.110 align:middle line:84%
And everything has to be--
it's like an experiment.

00:14:47.110 --> 00:14:48.790 align:middle line:90%
You do an experiment.

00:14:48.790 --> 00:14:53.380 align:middle line:84%
Your colleague has to be able to
replicate exactly what you did

00:14:53.380 --> 00:14:55.120 align:middle line:84%
and come to the
same conclusions.

00:14:55.120 --> 00:15:00.760 align:middle line:84%
Furthermore, everything is
open to peer group critique.

00:15:00.760 --> 00:15:02.800 align:middle line:84%
And that's always been
the way of the Torah.

00:15:02.800 --> 00:15:06.230 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the Talmud
specifically,

00:15:06.230 --> 00:15:13.910 align:middle line:84%
which is an ongoing live
discussion of everything that's

00:15:13.910 --> 00:15:19.480 align:middle line:84%
written in the binary code,
of how to understand it

00:15:19.480 --> 00:15:22.110 align:middle line:90%
and how to apply that.

00:15:22.110 --> 00:15:31.540 align:middle line:84%
And that code is essentially--
the whole methodology

00:15:31.540 --> 00:15:36.240 align:middle line:84%
is what can only be learned
from a teacher who learned it

00:15:36.240 --> 00:15:39.045 align:middle line:84%
from his teacher,
from his master.

00:15:39.045 --> 00:15:42.440 align:middle line:84%
Even though it's written
down, here's the thing,

00:15:42.440 --> 00:15:44.520 align:middle line:84%
someone could pick
up-- and the Talmud

00:15:44.520 --> 00:15:46.634 align:middle line:84%
has been translated
into English.

00:15:46.634 --> 00:15:47.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:15:47.300 --> 00:15:48.470 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to get into
that in a second--

00:15:48.470 --> 00:15:48.780 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: But anyone--

00:15:48.780 --> 00:15:49.738 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: But go ahead.

00:15:49.738 --> 00:15:51.630 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: --who
opens it up is going

00:15:51.630 --> 00:15:57.440 align:middle line:84%
to be lost immediately because
it requires apprenticeship.

00:15:57.440 --> 00:16:00.071 align:middle line:84%
It requires years and
decades of studying--

00:16:00.071 --> 00:16:01.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: To be able to read--

00:16:01.320 --> 00:16:02.350 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: --by a master--

00:16:02.350 --> 00:16:03.510 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --the layers
under the layers.

00:16:03.510 --> 00:16:04.000 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yes.

00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:04.270 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:16:04.270 --> 00:16:06.090 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: And even to
start with, the Torah

00:16:06.090 --> 00:16:07.414 align:middle line:90%
does not talk on one level.

00:16:07.414 --> 00:16:08.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:16:08.080 --> 00:16:11.250 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: It's well-known
the Torah has four levels--

00:16:11.250 --> 00:16:13.380 align:middle line:90%
dimensions of exploration.

00:16:13.380 --> 00:16:16.204 align:middle line:84%
And I'm purposely not using
the word "interpretation."

00:16:16.204 --> 00:16:17.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exploration.

00:16:17.120 --> 00:16:17.620 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: OK?

00:16:17.620 --> 00:16:18.180 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:16:18.180 --> 00:16:20.750 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: If you have
scientific fact,

00:16:20.750 --> 00:16:23.850 align:middle line:84%
you're not making
an interpretation.

00:16:23.850 --> 00:16:25.030 align:middle line:90%
That is the fact.

00:16:25.030 --> 00:16:26.830 align:middle line:90%
Those are the facts of physics.

00:16:26.830 --> 00:16:33.540 align:middle line:84%
And so when the Talmudic mind,
when the Talmudists-- now,

00:16:33.540 --> 00:16:37.120 align:middle line:84%
every Talmudist in the ancient
times, not so long ago,

00:16:37.120 --> 00:16:39.330 align:middle line:90%
was also a Kabbalist.

00:16:39.330 --> 00:16:44.170 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, and this
is not very well-known,

00:16:44.170 --> 00:16:49.480 align:middle line:84%
about a quarter to a third of
the whole Talmud is Kabbalah.

00:16:49.480 --> 00:16:51.920 align:middle line:90%
But it is so well-concealed.

00:16:51.920 --> 00:16:53.670 align:middle line:90%
It's hidden in stories.

00:16:53.670 --> 00:16:55.320 align:middle line:90%
It's hidden in aphorisms.

00:16:55.320 --> 00:16:57.270 align:middle line:84%
It's hidden in things
that look like legends

00:16:57.270 --> 00:16:59.540 align:middle line:84%
of the Jews, things that
look like fairy tales.

00:16:59.540 --> 00:17:01.791 align:middle line:90%
The masters were so clever.

00:17:01.791 --> 00:17:02.290 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:17:02.290 --> 00:17:05.079 align:middle line:90%
They're masters of cryptology.

00:17:05.079 --> 00:17:07.079 align:middle line:84%
And so if you have
something that's

00:17:07.079 --> 00:17:09.484 align:middle line:84%
so precious, so
profound, something

00:17:09.484 --> 00:17:11.579 align:middle line:84%
that's coming from
another dimension,

00:17:11.579 --> 00:17:14.000 align:middle line:90%
and you have to transmit it.

00:17:14.000 --> 00:17:18.319 align:middle line:84%
But you have to be very
careful to protect it

00:17:18.319 --> 00:17:24.130 align:middle line:84%
and not to allow those that
are not fitting to access it

00:17:24.130 --> 00:17:25.510 align:middle line:90%
or that would abuse it--

00:17:25.510 --> 00:17:26.319 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Denigrate
it in some way.

00:17:26.319 --> 00:17:27.902 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: --and
denigrate it like that.

00:17:27.902 --> 00:17:33.160 align:middle line:84%
So you have to be able to
teach it, pass it down in a way

00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:36.840 align:middle line:84%
that the information
is there, but it's not

00:17:36.840 --> 00:17:40.170 align:middle line:84%
readily observable, knowable,
to anyone from the outside

00:17:40.170 --> 00:17:42.310 align:middle line:84%
until you know the code
of how to break it.

00:17:42.310 --> 00:17:43.940 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:17:43.940 --> 00:17:45.200 align:middle line:90%
That makes sense.

00:17:45.200 --> 00:17:48.280 align:middle line:84%
And so now there are,
certainly in recent times

00:17:48.280 --> 00:17:51.480 align:middle line:84%
and, again, like
what Madonna did

00:17:51.480 --> 00:17:55.590 align:middle line:84%
for bringing the Kabbalah
to our awareness,

00:17:55.590 --> 00:17:57.740 align:middle line:84%
you might say Dan
Brown did with a lot

00:17:57.740 --> 00:18:00.540 align:middle line:84%
of the mystical Christian
teachings, so to speak.

00:18:00.540 --> 00:18:04.140 align:middle line:84%
And again, this notion of
scholars throughout the past

00:18:04.140 --> 00:18:06.950 align:middle line:84%
being involved in the
reinterpretation--

00:18:06.950 --> 00:18:09.620 align:middle line:84%
in this case, a
reinterpretation.

00:18:09.620 --> 00:18:12.520 align:middle line:84%
So you're saying that
even just looking

00:18:12.520 --> 00:18:14.630 align:middle line:84%
at something like
the King James Bible,

00:18:14.630 --> 00:18:16.860 align:middle line:84%
for example, and the
interpretations that took place

00:18:16.860 --> 00:18:20.800 align:middle line:84%
during that period of time
with the Christian texts, which

00:18:20.800 --> 00:18:23.880 align:middle line:84%
were primarily-- I mean,
my understanding-- as more

00:18:23.880 --> 00:18:25.160 align:middle line:90%
politically motivated.

00:18:25.160 --> 00:18:28.900 align:middle line:84%
There are certain parts that no
longer exist in the Christian

00:18:28.900 --> 00:18:30.050 align:middle line:90%
Bible.

00:18:30.050 --> 00:18:33.070 align:middle line:84%
You're saying that in
the Talmud, in the Torah,

00:18:33.070 --> 00:18:34.310 align:middle line:90%
this is not the case.

00:18:34.310 --> 00:18:39.110 align:middle line:84%
There haven't been severe edits,
edits for political expediency

00:18:39.110 --> 00:18:40.320 align:middle line:90%
and such throughout history.

00:18:40.320 --> 00:18:42.189 align:middle line:84%
It stayed in a pure
state this whole time?

00:18:42.189 --> 00:18:43.230 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: That is correct.

00:18:43.230 --> 00:18:49.880 align:middle line:84%
In fact, even if there was a
dispute, an argument about any

00:18:49.880 --> 00:18:54.180 align:middle line:84%
of the thousands of
matters, the minority view

00:18:54.180 --> 00:18:57.420 align:middle line:90%
is always kept alive.

00:18:57.420 --> 00:19:01.220 align:middle line:84%
It may not be the one that's
most applicable at any given

00:19:01.220 --> 00:19:02.630 align:middle line:90%
time and place.

00:19:02.630 --> 00:19:06.230 align:middle line:84%
But the minority view
is never discarded,

00:19:06.230 --> 00:19:09.524 align:middle line:84%
and it is given as much
validity as the majority view--

00:19:09.524 --> 00:19:10.440 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That's good.

00:19:10.440 --> 00:19:17.280 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: --because if the proper
methodology is applied, then

00:19:17.280 --> 00:19:21.520 align:middle line:84%
it is also reflecting
the spiritual truth.

00:19:21.520 --> 00:19:24.140 align:middle line:84%
The whole Torah is
higher dimensionality

00:19:24.140 --> 00:19:28.610 align:middle line:84%
that is now being manifest
into our lower dimension.

00:19:28.610 --> 00:19:30.679 align:middle line:90%
Very difficult thing to do.

00:19:30.679 --> 00:19:31.220 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:19:31.220 --> 00:19:32.678 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: It's like
literally trying

00:19:32.678 --> 00:19:34.980 align:middle line:84%
to get an elephant through
the eye of a needle.

00:19:34.980 --> 00:19:37.470 align:middle line:84%
So when we come
into this dimension,

00:19:37.470 --> 00:19:39.420 align:middle line:90%
we have to go right or left.

00:19:39.420 --> 00:19:41.150 align:middle line:90%
We have to make choices here.

00:19:41.150 --> 00:19:42.510 align:middle line:90%
We're in a higher dimension.

00:19:42.510 --> 00:19:46.525 align:middle line:84%
Both aspects can co-exist
and do exist simultaneously.

00:19:46.525 --> 00:19:47.330 align:middle line:90%
And no problem.

00:19:47.330 --> 00:19:47.913 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:19:47.913 --> 00:19:50.820 align:middle line:84%
We have more duality
in this level.

00:19:50.820 --> 00:19:52.630 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: But this
is the beauty of it.

00:19:52.630 --> 00:19:56.015 align:middle line:90%
Nothing is ever rejected.

00:19:56.015 --> 00:19:57.750 align:middle line:84%
You have to know how
to play the game.

00:19:57.750 --> 00:19:58.650 align:middle line:90%
It's a master game.

00:19:58.650 --> 00:20:01.660 align:middle line:84%
Once you learn the
techniques, you can join it.

00:20:01.660 --> 00:20:04.910 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, it's
a master game that

00:20:04.910 --> 00:20:06.530 align:middle line:84%
goes on throughout
the generations

00:20:06.530 --> 00:20:10.230 align:middle line:84%
and never really even stopped,
even though the basic parts had

00:20:10.230 --> 00:20:11.060 align:middle line:90%
been written down.

00:20:11.060 --> 00:20:17.440 align:middle line:84%
It is the original internet
that spans across millennia.

00:20:17.440 --> 00:20:19.690 align:middle line:90%
It's really quite astounding.

00:20:19.690 --> 00:20:25.380 align:middle line:84%
And the Talmud covers
literally every single subject

00:20:25.380 --> 00:20:27.410 align:middle line:90%
that we could possibly imagine.

00:20:27.410 --> 00:20:29.060 align:middle line:90%
It's not just Jewish law.

00:20:29.060 --> 00:20:30.930 align:middle line:90%
It's philosophy, theology.

00:20:30.930 --> 00:20:32.200 align:middle line:90%
It's psychology.

00:20:32.200 --> 00:20:33.965 align:middle line:90%
It's sexuality.

00:20:33.965 --> 00:20:34.590 align:middle line:90%
It's sociology.

00:20:34.590 --> 00:20:35.550 align:middle line:90%


00:20:35.550 --> 00:20:41.610 align:middle line:84%
It deals with everyday
life issues and problems.

00:20:41.610 --> 00:20:44.770 align:middle line:84%
It deals with issues between
men and women and parents

00:20:44.770 --> 00:20:45.910 align:middle line:90%
and children.

00:20:45.910 --> 00:20:47.910 align:middle line:90%
It's all in there.

00:20:47.910 --> 00:20:52.730 align:middle line:84%
But if one develops and
has the eyes to see,

00:20:52.730 --> 00:20:59.370 align:middle line:84%
this is all echoing higher
dimensionality, how it now

00:20:59.370 --> 00:21:04.230 align:middle line:84%
manifests into our everyday
existence which then enables

00:21:04.230 --> 00:21:10.020 align:middle line:84%
us to reunite our lower
dimensionality back

00:21:10.020 --> 00:21:12.950 align:middle line:84%
in with the higher
dimensionality.

00:21:12.950 --> 00:21:15.100 align:middle line:84%
And in fact, even
the Torah that we

00:21:15.100 --> 00:21:18.256 align:middle line:84%
have now-- the
written Torah, as it

00:21:18.256 --> 00:21:21.830 align:middle line:84%
was revealed at Mount
Sinai-- in itself

00:21:21.830 --> 00:21:28.600 align:middle line:84%
is a lower dimensional replica
of a higher-dimensional Torah,

00:21:28.600 --> 00:21:31.950 align:middle line:84%
which, as I said earlier,
is really the mind of God.

00:21:31.950 --> 00:21:36.630 align:middle line:84%
It's God's own consciousness
that he is projecting

00:21:36.630 --> 00:21:39.030 align:middle line:90%
into this lower dimension.

00:21:39.030 --> 00:21:42.500 align:middle line:84%
The assumption here is that this
lower dimension was actually

00:21:42.500 --> 00:21:44.520 align:middle line:90%
part of the higher dimension.

00:21:44.520 --> 00:21:45.990 align:middle line:90%
Something fell out.

00:21:45.990 --> 00:21:46.970 align:middle line:90%
That's the famous--

00:21:46.970 --> 00:21:48.636 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That story
goes throughout all

00:21:48.636 --> 00:21:49.730 align:middle line:90%
of the world's traditions.

00:21:49.730 --> 00:21:50.480 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yes, yes.

00:21:50.480 --> 00:21:53.010 align:middle line:84%
But basically, we're all trying
to get back to the garden.

00:21:53.010 --> 00:21:53.490 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:21:53.490 --> 00:21:53.960 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: OK?

00:21:53.960 --> 00:21:54.710 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:21:54.710 --> 00:21:57.540 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: And that
we're trying to find

00:21:57.540 --> 00:22:02.610 align:middle line:84%
our roots, our individual and
collective roots, in what's

00:22:02.610 --> 00:22:05.470 align:middle line:84%
referred to in the common
law as the higher dimensional

00:22:05.470 --> 00:22:10.530 align:middle line:84%
body of Adam, the original
Adam, who was-- very important,

00:22:10.530 --> 00:22:12.310 align:middle line:90%
the term "Adam" is androgynous.

00:22:12.310 --> 00:22:14.660 align:middle line:90%
That's male and female.

00:22:14.660 --> 00:22:17.720 align:middle line:84%
Every human being is
like a cell in that body.

00:22:17.720 --> 00:22:21.390 align:middle line:84%
Every animal is part of that
body in every vegetable, plant,

00:22:21.390 --> 00:22:22.850 align:middle line:90%
and mineral.

00:22:22.850 --> 00:22:25.826 align:middle line:84%
The Jewish vision from
the very beginning,

00:22:25.826 --> 00:22:31.490 align:middle line:84%
from the get go, before there
was any idea of global unity

00:22:31.490 --> 00:22:34.500 align:middle line:84%
and we're all one family-- OK,
we're talking about thousands

00:22:34.500 --> 00:22:35.680 align:middle line:90%
of years ago.

00:22:35.680 --> 00:22:39.030 align:middle line:84%
And if you read the words of
the prophets, it's very evident.

00:22:39.030 --> 00:22:41.540 align:middle line:84%
All reality, our
humanity, is viewed

00:22:41.540 --> 00:22:45.580 align:middle line:90%
as a single Adamic-like form.

00:22:45.580 --> 00:22:47.400 align:middle line:90%
We're all cells in that body.

00:22:47.400 --> 00:22:50.080 align:middle line:84%
And the whole purpose,
the modus operandi

00:22:50.080 --> 00:22:54.760 align:middle line:84%
of this very existence, is
to bring all the parts back

00:22:54.760 --> 00:22:56.430 align:middle line:84%
into the whole,
and then the whole

00:22:56.430 --> 00:22:58.630 align:middle line:84%
is greater than the sum
of the individual parts.

00:22:58.630 --> 00:23:04.270 align:middle line:84%
And then we have what is
known as the Messianic Era.

00:23:04.270 --> 00:23:07.960 align:middle line:84%
The Messianic Era, which
is very, very fundamental,

00:23:07.960 --> 00:23:10.770 align:middle line:84%
is it's not mythology,
and it is not legends.

00:23:10.770 --> 00:23:14.100 align:middle line:84%
This is really what we're
all aspiring towards.

00:23:14.100 --> 00:23:18.540 align:middle line:84%
This is when we
become, once again,

00:23:18.540 --> 00:23:25.270 align:middle line:84%
this single consciousness slash
reality going back to-- we're

00:23:25.270 --> 00:23:29.260 align:middle line:84%
coming full circle
back to where we began.

00:23:29.260 --> 00:23:33.049 align:middle line:90%
So Talmud is the oral Torah.

00:23:33.049 --> 00:23:33.590 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:23:33.590 --> 00:23:36.030 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: The written Torah would
be like the left brain of God.

00:23:36.030 --> 00:23:36.571 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:23:36.571 --> 00:23:40.737 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: The Talmud would be
like the right brain of God.

00:23:40.737 --> 00:23:41.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, great.

00:23:41.570 --> 00:23:43.000 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: And the
corpus callosum?

00:23:43.000 --> 00:23:45.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes?

00:23:45.120 --> 00:23:48.570 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: When I learned
Torah, I become, in effect,

00:23:48.570 --> 00:23:50.370 align:middle line:90%
the cosmic corpus callosum.

00:23:50.370 --> 00:23:51.330 align:middle line:90%
I am bridging.

00:23:51.330 --> 00:23:54.870 align:middle line:84%
I am uniting together the
cosmic left and right brains,

00:23:54.870 --> 00:23:58.880 align:middle line:84%
the written Torah with the oral
Torah, and this creates unity.

00:23:58.880 --> 00:24:01.943 align:middle line:84%
This creates a profound harmony,
and this is called tikkun.

00:24:01.943 --> 00:24:04.030 align:middle line:84%
"Tikkun" is perhaps
the most important word

00:24:04.030 --> 00:24:05.530 align:middle line:90%
in the Jewish tradition.

00:24:05.530 --> 00:24:10.300 align:middle line:90%
It means rectification, fixing.

00:24:10.300 --> 00:24:14.380 align:middle line:84%
The whole purpose is
to fix, to mend that

00:24:14.380 --> 00:24:18.009 align:middle line:90%
which has been torn asunder.

00:24:18.009 --> 00:24:18.550 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:24:18.550 --> 00:24:22.910 align:middle line:84%
Now let's start weaving
in, as the overlay,

00:24:22.910 --> 00:24:27.640 align:middle line:84%
I suppose, or maybe the
underpinnings, the Kabbalah.

00:24:27.640 --> 00:24:28.400 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: OK.

00:24:28.400 --> 00:24:31.690 align:middle line:84%
So what does the
word "Kabbalah" mean?

00:24:31.690 --> 00:24:33.310 align:middle line:84%
Kabbalah simply
means that which has

00:24:33.310 --> 00:24:38.320 align:middle line:84%
been received, orally from
teacher all the way going back

00:24:38.320 --> 00:24:39.230 align:middle line:90%
to Moses.

00:24:39.230 --> 00:24:43.140 align:middle line:84%
And let me just emphasize
also, my tradition

00:24:43.140 --> 00:24:47.370 align:middle line:84%
goes back not just to
Moses on Mount Sinai,

00:24:47.370 --> 00:24:50.470 align:middle line:84%
but back to Abraham, Isaac, and
Jacob and to the matriarchs,

00:24:50.470 --> 00:24:55.260 align:middle line:84%
and even further back to
great-great-grandfather

00:24:55.260 --> 00:24:57.950 align:middle line:84%
Enoch, the seventh
generation from Adam.

00:24:57.950 --> 00:25:01.360 align:middle line:84%
And as astounding
as it may sound,

00:25:01.360 --> 00:25:03.920 align:middle line:84%
I'm able to trace my
tradition and my teachings

00:25:03.920 --> 00:25:06.900 align:middle line:84%
back to Adam, to
the original Adam.

00:25:06.900 --> 00:25:10.940 align:middle line:84%
So Kabbalah means that
which has been received.

00:25:10.940 --> 00:25:15.210 align:middle line:84%
And originally, the entire
oral Torah was called Kabbalah.

00:25:15.210 --> 00:25:17.400 align:middle line:90%
That's not very well-known.

00:25:17.400 --> 00:25:19.370 align:middle line:84%
There was the
written, and there was

00:25:19.370 --> 00:25:25.090 align:middle line:84%
that which was the
Kabbalah received orally.

00:25:25.090 --> 00:25:29.090 align:middle line:84%
As I mentioned, beginning
around the second century,

00:25:29.090 --> 00:25:33.000 align:middle line:84%
due to various sociological,
historical factors,

00:25:33.000 --> 00:25:34.510 align:middle line:90%
it started to be written down.

00:25:34.510 --> 00:25:37.020 align:middle line:84%
The last part of the oral
tradition to be written down

00:25:37.020 --> 00:25:38.539 align:middle line:84%
was what we now
call the Kabbalah.

00:25:38.539 --> 00:25:39.080 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:25:39.080 --> 00:25:43.150 align:middle line:84%
Now, this is where the science
is woven in as well, not just

00:25:43.150 --> 00:25:48.280 align:middle line:84%
the rules or laws that help
govern society and philosophy

00:25:48.280 --> 00:25:48.920 align:middle line:90%
and so forth.

00:25:48.920 --> 00:25:51.940 align:middle line:84%
But now we're talking
numbers, geometry,

00:25:51.940 --> 00:25:54.210 align:middle line:84%
all of these other
aspects of code, right?

00:25:54.210 --> 00:25:55.850 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yes, yes.

00:25:55.850 --> 00:25:58.320 align:middle line:84%
The Kabbalah, as I mentioned
earlier, is so vast.

00:25:58.320 --> 00:26:02.482 align:middle line:84%
It is not an exaggeration to say
it's like the word "science,"

00:26:02.482 --> 00:26:04.190 align:middle line:84%
which could mean so
many different things

00:26:04.190 --> 00:26:05.101 align:middle line:90%
to different people.

00:26:05.101 --> 00:26:05.600 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:26:05.600 --> 00:26:09.920 align:middle line:84%
So the Kabbalah is
the oral tradition.

00:26:09.920 --> 00:26:15.320 align:middle line:84%
But specifically, it
is the esoteric aspect

00:26:15.320 --> 00:26:16.979 align:middle line:90%
of the oral tradition.

00:26:16.979 --> 00:26:17.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:26:17.520 --> 00:26:19.510 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: Here's another
way to understand it.

00:26:19.510 --> 00:26:21.460 align:middle line:90%
The written Torah is the body.

00:26:21.460 --> 00:26:22.759 align:middle line:90%
The oral Torah is the soul.

00:26:22.759 --> 00:26:23.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:26:23.300 --> 00:26:24.650 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: OK?

00:26:24.650 --> 00:26:26.720 align:middle line:90%
There's a soul to the soul.

00:26:26.720 --> 00:26:28.250 align:middle line:90%
That's the Kabbalah.

00:26:28.250 --> 00:26:30.140 align:middle line:84%
What is now known
in the world-- we

00:26:30.140 --> 00:26:33.460 align:middle line:90%
said the cat's out of the bag.

00:26:33.460 --> 00:26:35.787 align:middle line:90%
There's so many species of cats.

00:26:35.787 --> 00:26:36.370 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:26:36.370 --> 00:26:38.920 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: There's domesticated
cats, and there's wild cats.

00:26:38.920 --> 00:26:44.180 align:middle line:84%
And they're still finding new
species of feline creatures.

00:26:44.180 --> 00:26:49.640 align:middle line:84%
So the term "Kabbalah"
almost doesn't mean anything

00:26:49.640 --> 00:26:53.810 align:middle line:84%
because it can mean
so many things.

00:26:53.810 --> 00:26:57.420 align:middle line:84%
It is, in general,
the inner soul.

00:26:57.420 --> 00:27:00.130 align:middle line:84%
Look, we're all
spiritually-based people here,

00:27:00.130 --> 00:27:03.800 align:middle line:84%
anyone who's listening,
and we have to assume that.

00:27:03.800 --> 00:27:04.840 align:middle line:90%
We know we have a body.

00:27:04.840 --> 00:27:06.000 align:middle line:90%
We know we have a soul.

00:27:06.000 --> 00:27:07.570 align:middle line:90%
And Torah is no different.

00:27:07.570 --> 00:27:12.220 align:middle line:84%
It has the external aspect,
and it has the internal aspect.

00:27:12.220 --> 00:27:13.190 align:middle line:90%
They are not separate.

00:27:13.190 --> 00:27:16.630 align:middle line:84%
In fact, they fit
together isomorphically,

00:27:16.630 --> 00:27:21.020 align:middle line:90%
like a hand inside of a glove.

00:27:21.020 --> 00:27:25.490 align:middle line:84%
When one learns Torah,
it is a process.

00:27:25.490 --> 00:27:27.000 align:middle line:90%
It's not academic learning.

00:27:27.000 --> 00:27:29.120 align:middle line:84%
You are actually
becoming a partner

00:27:29.120 --> 00:27:30.660 align:middle line:90%
with the divine mind itself.

00:27:30.660 --> 00:27:33.100 align:middle line:84%
As I mentioned, I
become, in effect,

00:27:33.100 --> 00:27:37.260 align:middle line:84%
this cosmic corpus
callosum bridging together

00:27:37.260 --> 00:27:40.740 align:middle line:84%
the left side of creation with
the right side of creation.

00:27:40.740 --> 00:27:44.190 align:middle line:84%
This is, in general, what
the Kabbalah is doing.

00:27:44.190 --> 00:27:48.380 align:middle line:84%
It's simply adding
to the unification

00:27:48.380 --> 00:27:50.560 align:middle line:84%
from the left side
and the right side.

00:27:50.560 --> 00:27:52.100 align:middle line:84%
Because the more
that we understand

00:27:52.100 --> 00:27:54.480 align:middle line:84%
about the soul,
strangely enough,

00:27:54.480 --> 00:27:58.520 align:middle line:84%
the more we have the capacity
to understand about the body

00:27:58.520 --> 00:28:02.147 align:middle line:84%
and how it functions, which
is still so much of a mystery.

00:28:02.147 --> 00:28:02.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:28:02.730 --> 00:28:05.230 align:middle line:84%
And we're going to get into
one of those primary seats

00:28:05.230 --> 00:28:05.730 align:middle line:90%
eventually--

00:28:05.730 --> 00:28:06.704 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: Yes, yes, yes.

00:28:06.704 --> 00:28:07.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: --in a little bit.

00:28:07.870 --> 00:28:10.530 align:middle line:90%
But I wonder this.

00:28:10.530 --> 00:28:13.260 align:middle line:84%
As you were talking about the
oral Torah, the written Torah,

00:28:13.260 --> 00:28:16.970 align:middle line:84%
the Talmud, and then
the Kabbalah overlay,

00:28:16.970 --> 00:28:20.380 align:middle line:84%
is this true in other of the
world's ancient traditions

00:28:20.380 --> 00:28:22.040 align:middle line:84%
as well, where you
have an oral and you

00:28:22.040 --> 00:28:26.790 align:middle line:84%
have a written and similar
cosmic principles flowing

00:28:26.790 --> 00:28:27.930 align:middle line:90%
through?

00:28:27.930 --> 00:28:31.010 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: Regina, I'll
answer you this way.

00:28:31.010 --> 00:28:33.050 align:middle line:90%
There very may well have been.

00:28:33.050 --> 00:28:35.531 align:middle line:90%


00:28:35.531 --> 00:28:36.030 align:middle line:90%
But today--

00:28:36.030 --> 00:28:37.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: But it's not-- yeah.

00:28:37.280 --> 00:28:40.210 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: --where are the
living oral traditions

00:28:40.210 --> 00:28:44.790 align:middle line:84%
that can be legitimately
traced back?

00:28:44.790 --> 00:28:47.610 align:middle line:84%
This is what I learned
from my teacher.

00:28:47.610 --> 00:28:51.000 align:middle line:84%
Someone could say I studied
from my teacher for 10, 20,

00:28:51.000 --> 00:28:51.790 align:middle line:90%
30 years.

00:28:51.790 --> 00:28:52.810 align:middle line:90%
He studied from his.

00:28:52.810 --> 00:28:54.030 align:middle line:90%
We know who that person is.

00:28:54.030 --> 00:28:55.780 align:middle line:84%
And then we can trace
it all the way back.

00:28:55.780 --> 00:28:56.280 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:28:56.280 --> 00:28:59.530 align:middle line:84%
Is anyone from any
religion, mystical group,

00:28:59.530 --> 00:29:01.530 align:middle line:84%
society can come
forward and say, here,

00:29:01.530 --> 00:29:04.099 align:middle line:84%
I have an ancient
tradition together

00:29:04.099 --> 00:29:05.140 align:middle line:90%
with a written tradition.

00:29:05.140 --> 00:29:07.267 align:middle line:84%
Now, together with
this, the problem

00:29:07.267 --> 00:29:09.350 align:middle line:84%
is compounded because
there's many traditions that

00:29:09.350 --> 00:29:10.480 align:middle line:90%
have no written tradition.

00:29:10.480 --> 00:29:10.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:29:10.780 --> 00:29:11.720 align:middle line:90%
>>BAKST: It's only oral.

00:29:11.720 --> 00:29:12.386 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:29:12.386 --> 00:29:13.940 align:middle line:84%
>>BAKST: And then
we have fragments

00:29:13.940 --> 00:29:17.857 align:middle line:84%
of written traditions, but
there's no oral tradition

00:29:17.857 --> 00:29:18.440 align:middle line:90%
to go with it.

00:29:18.440 --> 00:29:20.000 align:middle line:90%
That's been lost.

00:29:20.000 --> 00:29:21.920 align:middle line:90%
So it's almost moot.

00:29:21.920 --> 00:29:22.420 align:middle line:90%
OK.

